data.enText: a country consisting of a group of individual states that have control over their own affairs but are controlled by a central government for national decisions, etc.
a group of clubs, trade/labor unions , etc. that have joined together to form an organization
the act of forming a federation

data.chText: 许多议会议员反对欧洲结成联邦。
data.enText: Many MPs are against federation in Europe.

simple_means.memory_skill: feder 联盟 + ation 行为，结果 → 联盟

tr: the act of constituting a political unity out of a number of separate states or colonies or provinces so that each member retains the management of its internal affairs
an organization formed by merging several groups or parties

value.def: A federation is a group of societies or other organizations which have joined together, usually because they share a common interest.

example.ex: The organization emerged from a federation of six national agencies.
example.tran: 该组织由 6 个全国性机构联合而成。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft in names

value.tran: (社团或组织的)同盟，联盟，联合会

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + feder 联盟 + ate 做，造成，使… → 共结联盟 →〔使〕联盟
feder 联盟 + al …的 → 联邦的
federal 联邦的 + ism …制度 → 联邦制
feder 联盟 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 联盟
